{"cursor":"4599","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Chiral resolution' in stereochemistry is a process for the separation of\nracemic compounds into their enantiomers. It is an important tool in\nthe production of optically active drugs. Other terms with the same meaning are\n'optical resolution' and 'mechanical resolution'.\n\nOne disadvantage of chiral resolution of racemates compared to direct asymmetric\nsynthesis of one of the enantiomers is that only 50% of a desired enantiomer is\nobtained. Several methods exist.\n","linknr":171,"url":"Chiral_resolution","recorded":1362901652,"links":18,"instances":[],"pdf":["http://www.iupac.org/publications/pac/1991/pdf/6308x1119.pdf","http://www.iupac.org/publications/pac/1991/pdf/6308x1119.pdf"],"categories":["Stereochemistry"],"headings":["Resolution by crystallization","Chiral resolving agents","Chiral column chromatography","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/RRRsynthesis.png/400px-RRRsynthesis.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Stereochemistry","Racemic","Enantiomer","Optically_active","Drug","Asymmetric_synthesis","Enantiopure","Louis_Pasteur","Optical_activity","Tartaric_acid","Seed_crystal","Supersaturation","Tartrate","Methadone","Petroleum_ether","Ethanol","Hydrobenzoin","Optical_purity","Diastereomer","Physical_chemistry","Amine","Carboxylic_acid","Chiral_resolving_agent","Tartaric_acid","Brucine","Louis_Pasteur","Tartaric_acid","Cinchotoxine","Organic_synthesis","Duloxetine","Racemic","Alcohol","Toluene","Methanol","Mandelic_acid","Diastereomer","Sodium_hydroxide","Epimerization","Hydrochloric_acid","Chiral_column_chromatography"]}